TASK_DESCRIPTION=Running any unknown doey command (e.g. 'doey wazzup?') triggers the intent fallback which crashes with 'error: unknown option --reasoning-effort'. This was introduced in task #463 which added --reasoning-effort low to the Opus call. The installed Claude CLI does not support this flag. Fix: remove the --reasoning-effort flag from intent-fallback.sh / doey-headless.sh. The fallback must work without it.
